01:08:16,875 --> 01:08:20,590
I've always wanted
to make sure...

1089
01:08:20,673 --> 01:08:25,058
that I've loved you
and Terry absolutely equally.

1090
01:08:25,140 --> 01:08:27,896
Well, you have,
you-you absolutely have.

1091
01:08:28,940 --> 01:08:31,445
Dad, don't worry about a thing.

1092
01:08:31,529 --> 01:08:34,534
Everything's gonna be fine.

1093
01:08:34,618 --> 01:08:37,416
Everything's gonna be fine. I promise.

1094
01:08:37,498 --> 01:08:39,712
All right.

1095
01:08:44,471 --> 01:08:47,394
I thought I was pregnant.
It's a false alarm.

1096
01:08:47,477 --> 01:08:49,398
- Pregnant?
- Yeah.

1097
01:08:49,480 --> 01:08:53,030
- I was late. I'm never late, am I?
- But you're not. That's a relief.

1098
01:08:53,113 --> 01:08:55,034
Why?

1099
01:08:55,117 --> 01:08:57,998
I think it would be great.
We always talked about it.

1100
01:08:58,035 --> 01:08:58,750
Yeah, some day.

1101
01:08:58,791 --> 01:09:02,424
We can swing it. Now your
uncle's helped you out financially.

1102
01:09:02,507 --> 01:09:06,390
And you said that he might help you out
with that loan for that sport shop idea.

1103
01:09:08,143 --> 01:09:10,482
I think you'd make such a good dad.

1104
01:09:10,565 --> 01:09:15,617
And just think, if we had boys, you know, you
could teach them to play football or something.

1105
01:09:15,658 --> 01:09:17,621
Right.

1106
01:09:19,626 --> 01:09:21,879
- You're not hungry?
- Not really, love.

1107
01:09:21,915 --> 01:09:24,133
- It's very nice.
- It's your favorite.

1108
01:09:24,176 --> 01:09:27,599
I know. Can I get
a whiskey, please?

1109
01:09:29,269 --> 01:09:31,189
- A whiskey?
- Yeah.

1110
01:09:31,273 --> 01:09:34,321
- I don't know if we got any left.
- It's in my drawer.

1111
01:09:49,350 --> 01:09:52,524
- You're late.
- Sorry, sorry.

1112
01:09:52,606 --> 01:09:54,862
Oh, Jesus Christ.
You've been drinking.

1113
01:09:54,945 --> 01:09:59,162
I'm fine. I said I'm fine.
Just leave it at that, all right?

1114
01:09:59,204 --> 01:10:01,250
Let's just do it, Brother,
before I change my mind.

1115
01:10:01,332 --> 01:10:04,338
- Have you got the guns?
- Here. Right here. And the bullets.

1116
01:10:04,381 --> 01:10:06,635
All right, all right.
Don't load them now.

1117
01:10:06,719 --> 01:10:09,558
- Are you too drunk to handle this, Terry?
- I said I'm fine.

1118
01:10:09,640 --> 01:10:11,979
- All right, let's just go.
- Right.

1119
01:10:12,021 --> 01:10:14,359
We'll go up to him when
he's on his own, we shoot him...

1120
01:10:14,401 --> 01:10:16,655
and then I'll put a second one
in him just to make certain.

1121
01:10:16,697 --> 01:10:19,953
I know what to do, Ian. Right?
You don't always have to run things.

1122
01:10:20,038 --> 01:10:23,628
- Can you handle this, the state you're in?
- Worry about yourself.

1123
01:10:23,711 --> 01:10:27,009
All right? I'll take care of him. Just-

1124
01:10:27,051 --> 01:10:29,849
- Have you got the address?
- Yeah, I've got it. Let's get this over with.

1125
01:10:36,570 --> 01:10:39,243
Don't worry about the restaurant.

1126
01:10:39,326 --> 01:10:42,123
I can help you if you need me.

1127
01:10:46,465 --> 01:10:48,678
I dreamed about the boys last night.

1128
01:10:48,719 --> 01:10:50,683
Again?

1129
01:10:52,727 --> 01:10:55,608
When they were younger.

1130
01:11:13,644 --> 01:11:16,024
There he is.
Let's take him now.

1131
01:11:16,108 --> 01:11:18,696
Wait. You don't wanna let him
see his mum for the last time?

1132
01:11:18,779 --> 01:11:20,700
- What?
- You make me sick.

1133
01:11:20,783 --> 01:11:22,914
Let him see the old lady.

1134
01:11:22,996 --> 01:11:26,879
You're drunk, Terry. It's a disgrace
turning up on a job like this drunk.

1135
01:11:26,962 --> 01:11:29,133
Look, we've probably missed
our last opportunity now.

1136
01:11:29,218 --> 01:11:31,263
We'll get him
when he comes out.

1137
01:11:31,304 --> 01:11:35,480
Christ. You don't care about anyone
in this world except yourself.

1138
01:11:35,521 --> 01:11:38,653
You're not a big shot, Ian.
You're a small stakes player.

1139
01:11:38,736 --> 01:11:41,909
I don't care how many hotels you wind up
running or how hot that girl is.

1140
01:11:41,992 --> 01:11:43,955
Why don't you shut up?

1141
01:11:43,997 --> 01:11:47,295
I bet you had a big handful of those pills
that guy keeps you supplied with as well.

1142
01:11:47,379 --> 01:11:49,759
I'm fine.

1143
01:11:49,800 --> 01:11:51,971
We'll kill him
when he comes out.

1144
01:14:00,770 --> 01:14:03,150
- Mr. Burns.
- Hey?

1145
01:14:03,233 --> 01:14:05,906
Oh, that's right. I remember you.
We met at that, uh, party.

1146
01:14:05,947 --> 01:14:08,911
- Yeah. We-We thought it was you.
- I understand you're Howard Swann's nephews.

1147
01:14:08,954 --> 01:14:09,376
That's right.

1148
01:14:09,413 --> 01:14:11,333
What are you doing around here?
You live around here?

1149
01:14:11,417 --> 01:14:13,379
- No. Ian?
- Do it now.

1150
01:14:13,462 --> 01:14:15,425
- Let's just do it now.
- Hey, what's going on?

1151
01:14:15,466 --> 01:14:18,640
Terry, do it! Do it now!

1152
01:14:39,389 --> 01:14:41,478
What are you thinking?

1153
01:14:44,149 --> 01:14:46,112
That then was then.

1154
01:14:47,907 --> 01:14:50,078
And now is now.

1155
01:14:51,121 --> 01:14:53,709
And we've done it and it's over.

1156
01:14:56,005 --> 01:14:58,176
And it's always now.

1157
01:14:59,303 --> 01:15:02,644
It went much smoother
than I thought, Ian.

1158
01:15:02,685 --> 01:15:05,232
And not a soul around.

1159
01:15:05,316 --> 01:15:07,695
We're lucky he chose that path.

1160
01:15:07,779 --> 01:15:09,908
Yeah, no one saw us.

1161
01:15:09,991 --> 01:15:12,247
And we did the right thing.

1162
01:15:12,329 --> 01:15:15,754
We didn't run back to the car.
We just walked calmly back.

1163
01:15:15,837 --> 01:15:17,758
Yeah.

1164
01:15:17,841 --> 01:15:20,721
There's a great weight off my back.

1165
01:15:22,350 --> 01:15:24,479
You're right, Ian.

1166
01:15:24,564 --> 01:15:27,317
It's now.

1167
01:15:27,402 --> 01:15:29,656
It's always now.

1168
01:15:31,326 --> 01:15:33,915
You better burn his wallet.

1169
01:15:52,368 --> 01:15:54,999
- Are you okay?
- Go back to sleep.

1170
01:16:16,708 --> 01:16:18,838
- What do you think of this one?
- Oh, I love it.

1171
01:16:18,879 --> 01:16:22,887
I thought you would. So, are there
any new developments on California?

1172
01:16:22,971 --> 01:16:26,687
Yeah, I think we can leave in about four
or six weeks. We signed the papers today.

1173
01:16:26,770 --> 01:16:28,816
Great. Did you see in the papers...

1174
01:16:28,899 --> 01:16:33,075
that guy that you were speaking to
at the wrap party was murdered?

1175
01:16:33,158 --> 01:16:36,748
- Who?
- Martin- Martin Burns, was it?

1176
01:16:36,833 --> 01:16:39,421
Oh, really?
How bizarre.

1177
01:16:39,504 --> 01:16:42,343
Yeah, well, no one
saw or heard anything.

1178
01:16:42,427 --> 01:16:45,057
Didn't he have some association
with your uncle at one point?

1179
01:16:45,093 --> 01:16:45,808
I think he did, yeah.

1180
01:16:47,061 --> 01:16:49,858
- What do you think of this one?
- As if you have to ask.

1181
01:16:59,544 --> 01:17:03,886
You know, I'll never forget you boys,
what you did for me.

1182
01:17:03,970 --> 01:17:05,849
I owe you my life.

1183
01:17:05,974 --> 01:17:10,107
And the joy of repaying you
gives me such pleasure.

1184
01:17:10,191 --> 01:17:13,949
Now, Terry, you-
Look, you spoke about, uh...

1185
01:17:14,032 --> 01:17:18,499
you know, the notion of opening a-
a sports shop if you had the backing?

1186
01:17:18,583 --> 01:17:21,297
No, it's okay.

1187
01:17:21,380 --> 01:17:24,302
No, look. Look, cheer up.

1188
01:17:24,387 --> 01:17:29,061
The worst is behind you. I'm here
to tell you that the- the future is rosy.

1189
01:17:30,147 --> 01:17:32,402
Terry, Uncle Howard's right.

1190
01:17:32,484 --> 01:17:34,823
Stop walking around
with that face on.

1191
01:17:34,907 --> 01:17:38,372
This is your chance to get away
from that cheap idiot at the garage...

1192
01:17:38,455 --> 01:17:40,918
and make your own life.

1193
01:17:41,003 --> 01:17:43,047
- Where are they? Is that them?
- Yes.

1194
01:17:43,132 --> 01:17:47,181
- Angela, I'm so nervous.
- You're fine. They'll love you.

1195
01:17:47,222 --> 01:17:50,646
- Hello.
- Hello. Oh, it's nice to see you, sir. I'm Ian.

1196
01:17:50,730 --> 01:17:52,693
Nice to meet you.
Heard a lot about you.

1197
01:17:52,775 --> 01:17:55,615
- Hello. You have a nice trip?
- Very good, thank you.

1198
01:17:55,656 --> 01:17:58,120
- Let me take your bag.
- We've been really looking forward to this.

1199
01:17:58,202 --> 01:18:01,502
- Yeah, it'll be great.
- Your hair.

1200
01:18:01,543 --> 01:18:05,552
- So how's your play doing, love?
- It's going well. It's still selling out at weekends.

1201
01:18:05,588 --> 01:18:08,807
- Oh, well, that's to see you take your clothes off.
- Mom!

1202
01:18:08,892 --> 01:18:11,104
- So what do you do, Ian?
- Uh, hotels.

1203
01:18:11,188 --> 01:18:14,611
- Hotels? Which ones?
- Yeah, I got a couple in, uh, California.

1204
01:18:14,694 --> 01:18:17,576
Oh, yes, Angela said you were
planning an extended stay out there.

1205
01:18:17,660 --> 01:18:20,373
- Well, very extended, I hope.
- California.

1206
01:18:20,457 --> 01:18:22,377
I'm starving. Where are we eating?

1207
01:18:22,461 --> 01:18:25,509
- I'm taking you all to Claridge's.
- Oh, is it nice?

1208
01:18:25,592 --> 01:18:27,972
- Lovely.
- No, it's on us, though.

1209
01:18:28,013 --> 01:18:29,976
No, no, no.
This treat is on me. Yeah.

1210
01:18:30,017 --> 01:18:31,985
Oh, thank you.
Very nice of you.

1211
01:18:32,022 --> 01:18:34,151
Oh, they're really lovely,
your parents. Lovely.

1212
01:18:34,193 --> 01:18:36,405
- Oh, I can't get California out of my mind.
- I know.

1213
01:18:36,489 --> 01:18:40,622
I've spoken to Uncle Howard
and everything is right on track.

1214
01:18:43,544 --> 01:18:45,715
Thank you.

1215
01:18:45,798 --> 01:18:48,303
- She's beautiful, isn't she?
- Very, very.

1216
01:18:48,386 --> 01:18:51,017
A bit high maintenance, though.

1217
01:18:52,061 --> 01:18:55,735
- You up to it?
- I certainly hope so.

1218
01:18:55,818 --> 01:18:58,157
She could've had
the pick of any man, that girl.

1219
01:18:58,240 --> 01:19:00,661
Well, I realize I'm very lucky.
I do realize that.

1220
01:19:00,787 --> 01:19:06,716
I always dreaded the thought that she might
wind up with some starving actor in the theater.

1221
01:19:06,757 --> 01:19:09,262
Not that I've anything
against the theater, mind you...

1222
01:19:09,304 --> 01:19:14,522
but... a man who knows his way
around the world of business, well-

1223
01:19:14,606 --> 01:19:17,987
There was a time when I could've
invested in some ventures...

1224
01:19:18,072 --> 01:19:22,246
but I didn't have
the stomach for the risk.

1225
01:19:22,330 --> 01:19:27,758
So I spent my life behind the wheel
of a car driving other men.

1226
01:19:30,596 --> 01:19:33,268
She says you've got a future.

1227
01:19:36,484 --> 01:19:38,488
Oh, God.

1228
01:19:38,571 --> 01:19:41,284
- What is it?
- I can't take it.

1229
01:19:41,369 --> 01:19:44,250
- Take it easy. It's all right.
- I need another pill.

1230
01:19:44,291 --> 01:19:47,130
No, Terry. You can't take so many
of those, not with all that alcohol.

1231
01:19:47,213 --> 01:19:51,347
Kate, leave me alone.
I've gotta get rid of this feeling of panic.

1232
01:19:51,431 --> 01:19:54,144
- Why should you be feeling panicked?
- I don't know.

1233
01:19:54,228 --> 01:19:57,861
I just need the pill. Christ,
I can't even get a decent night's sleep.

1234
01:19:57,943 --> 01:20:00,322
All right.

1235
01:20:03,119 --> 01:20:05,624
My car didn't have that dent
when I brought it in.

1236
01:20:05,666 --> 01:20:09,007
- It had to have been there. Nobody's touched it.
- No, you put a dent in my car.

1237
01:20:09,090 --> 01:20:11,344
- How the hell would I dent it?
- I don't know.

1238
01:20:11,428 --> 01:20:12,101
What's going on?

1239
01:20:12,138 --> 01:20:14,684
There's a dent, look, in my car. Someone's driven my car.

1240
01:20:14,769 --> 01:20:17,440
- Will you shut up? What are you accusing me of?
- Someone has to have driven it.

1241
01:20:17,482 --> 01:20:19,444
Look where you point your finger.
It could get broken.

1242
01:20:19,486 --> 01:20:21,448
- Calm down. Calm down.
- Get your hands off me.

1243
01:20:21,490 --> 01:20:23,453
Sorry, Mr. Finn.
Just give us a minute.

1244
01:20:23,494 --> 01:20:25,456
I'll sort out
your bodywork for you.

1245
01:20:25,498 --> 01:20:28,087
I need a word with you.
What the hell's the matter with you?

1246
01:20:28,128 --> 01:20:32,220
Look, I'm not at all pleased with the way
things are going around here lately. All right?

1247
01:20:32,303 --> 01:20:34,599
Hey! There's another one here.

1248
01:20:37,522 --> 01:20:40,487
Yeah, I miss you too.

1249
01:20:40,528 --> 01:20:43,618
Nobu. Yeah, I made
reservations for after the show.

1250
01:20:44,577 --> 01:20:48,502
Who's that?
Look, I'll see you later. All right? Bye.

1251
01:20:51,174 --> 01:20:53,513
- Hey. Are you all right?
- I need to speak to you.

1252
01:20:53,554 --> 01:20:57,396
Well, I wish you'd called first. I'm expecting
some guys over for a conference call.

1253
01:20:57,478 --> 01:20:59,442
I'm having bad thoughts.

1254
01:20:59,525 --> 01:21:01,446
What kind of bad thoughts?

1255
01:21:03,950 --> 01:21:05,829
We did a terrible thing, Ian.

1256
01:21:05,912 --> 01:21:10,212
- Oh, Jesus, can you just get past it?
- I'm trying.

1257
01:21:10,296 --> 01:21:14,138
- I should never have let you talk me into it.
- I didn't.

1258
01:21:14,180 --> 01:21:18,019
Terry, you needed his help.
Loan sharks were gonna break your legs...

1259
01:21:18,102 --> 01:21:20,023
and maybe even Kate's as well.

1260
01:21:20,107 --> 01:21:22,863
But Martin Burns...

1261
01:21:22,904 --> 01:21:26,036
we stepped on him
like he was an insect.

1262
01:21:26,119 --> 01:21:28,290
Look, Terry,
I can't discuss this now.

1263
01:21:28,373 --> 01:21:32,465
I've got two guys and a transatlantic
conference call coming up.

1264
01:21:32,549 --> 01:21:35,221
I can't go on like this.

1265
01:21:35,262 --> 01:21:37,893
Let's talk about it later.
Why aren't you at the garage?

1266
01:21:37,976 --> 01:21:40,314
- I got let go.
- What does that mean?

1267
01:21:40,357 --> 01:21:46,243
The boss said,
uh, I-I should take some time off.

1268
01:21:46,284 --> 01:21:49,541
He thinks I've been under a lot of strain
lately. Thanks for denting the Jaguar.

1269
01:21:49,583 --> 01:21:53,090
Oh, I'm sorry.
I forgot to tell you.

1270
01:21:53,173 --> 01:21:56,847
Look. You've gotta relax. All right?

1271
01:21:56,931 --> 01:21:59,144
Lay off the booze and the pills.

1272
01:21:59,270 --> 01:22:01,148
No wonder you're
getting yourself in trouble.

1273
01:22:01,231 --> 01:22:03,235
I can't get through the day without drinking.

1274
01:22:03,319 --> 01:22:06,325
Look, you've got to go home.
All right? Rest up.

1275
01:22:06,408 --> 01:22:08,872
I'll call you later,
we'll get together, all right?

1276
01:22:08,913 --> 01:22:11,377
You've gotta ease up.
You'll give yourself a bloody heart attack.

1277
01:22:11,459 --> 01:22:13,423
Then I'll die. So I'll die.

1278
01:22:13,506 --> 01:22:16,304
Don't talk like that.
What's the matter with you?

1279
01:22:18,015 --> 01:22:20,144
- Guys, come in, please.
- Lovely.

1280
01:22:21,939 --> 01:22:25,070
Look, I'll call you later.
I'm gonna get you past this, okay?

1281
01:22:25,155 --> 01:22:27,242
All right.

1282
01:22:35,842 --> 01:22:38,179
See, this is more like it,
Terry, isn't it?

1283
01:22:38,263 --> 01:22:40,184
Getting out of the house.

1284
01:22:40,267 --> 01:22:44,609
Can't sit around there too much.
Too much thinking.

1285
01:22:44,652 --> 01:22:47,657
Kate said you're not even
talking about poker anymore.

1286
01:22:47,740 --> 01:22:49,661
Where's our old Terry?

1287
01:22:49,744 --> 01:22:52,083
- I mean, you're a gambler. This is you.
- Yeah.

1288
01:22:52,124 --> 01:22:54,295
I'm not suggesting you
go mad or anything, but-

1289
01:22:54,379 --> 01:22:56,759
I'm not the same Terry, Ian.

1290
01:22:56,801 --> 01:22:59,847
- I can't be anymore.
- No, you just have to focus.

1291
01:22:59,932 --> 01:23:02,103
Look, I-I been thinking
that you getting the sack...

1292
01:23:02,186 --> 01:23:04,316
is maybe the best thing
that ever happened to you.

1293
01:23:04,352 --> 01:23:04,441
What?

1294
01:23:04,524 --> 01:23:08,699
Yeah. Now is the perfect time to start
thinking about setting up the sport shop.

1295
01:23:08,783 --> 01:23:12,958
I mean, Uncle Howard said he would
start you off. You'd be your own boss.

1296
01:23:13,001 --> 01:23:17,258
No more kowtowing to
superiors. And you love sports.

1297
01:23:17,295 --> 01:23:17,633
I do.

1298
01:23:17,676 --> 01:23:21,266
Maybe you're right, Ian.
Maybe what I need is just a big change.

1299
01:23:21,350 --> 01:23:24,523
Yeah, you need to focus on something
substantial. You can't just do nothing.

1300
01:23:24,607 --> 01:23:26,610
- Yeah.
- Hey?

1301
01:23:26,652 --> 01:23:28,614
I think I'll do it, Ian.

1302
01:23:28,656 --> 01:23:31,662
Yeah, it's just exactly what you need, Terry.

1303
01:23:31,746 --> 01:23:36,129
Get off the booze and the pills
and set up your own place.

1304
01:23:36,171 --> 01:23:38,175
Right, and not just sporting goods.

1305
01:23:38,259 --> 01:23:40,179
Exercise equipment.

1306
01:23:40,263 --> 01:23:42,184
- That's where the money is today.
- Yeah?

1307
01:23:42,267 --> 01:23:45,190
Yeah. Helping people set up
their own private gyms and stuff.

1308
01:23:45,273 --> 01:23:47,194
I like the way
you're thinking, Terry.

1309
01:23:47,276 --> 01:23:49,614
'Cause you're thinking forwards.
You're not lookin' back.

1310
01:23:49,651 --> 01:23:50,115
That's right.

1311
01:23:50,199 --> 01:23:52,119
- You've got a really good future, Terry.
- Yeah?

1312
01:23:52,203 --> 01:23:55,417
You do. Listen, I'm not saying
that I haven't had moments...

1313
01:23:55,501 --> 01:23:58,131
where I've thought about what we've done,
and it's freaked me out.

1314
01:23:58,173 --> 01:24:00,177
- Go on!
- We were raised to know right from wrong.

1315
01:24:00,259 --> 01:24:02,181
- Go on!
- Did you get that one?

1316
01:24:02,264 --> 01:24:05,229
Look at this.
I got a winner.

1317
01:24:05,313 --> 01:24:07,901
It's the beginning
of a new streak, Terry.

1318
01:24:07,985 --> 01:24:09,905
I can feel it, Ian.

1319
01:24:13,705 --> 01:24:17,044
Could-Could you get this model
with the same interior in a left-hand drive...

1320
01:24:17,086 --> 01:24:20,551
- say, in California, for instance?
- For California. Yeah, certainly.

1321
01:24:20,635 --> 01:24:22,555
And would there be
a long waiting list or-

1322
01:24:22,639 --> 01:24:24,559
I would think about
three or four months.

1323
01:24:24,643 --> 01:24:27,149
- Oh, can I?
- Please do.

1324
01:24:40,591 --> 01:24:44,683
Hey, great scene.
You really nailed it.

1325
01:24:44,725 --> 01:24:48,148
- You were great. You were great tonight.
- Do you think so?

1326
01:24:49,360 --> 01:24:52,783
The bedroom scenes
were so sexy as always.

1327
01:24:52,867 --> 01:24:56,582
Well, I was doing it with him,
but I was thinking of you for motivation.

1328
01:25:00,255 --> 01:25:03,680
Don't forget. Tomorrow is Lord Eisley's party.
He's invited the whole cast.

1329
01:25:03,763 --> 01:25:05,975
Yeah. I'm gonna keep
my eye on you like a hawk.

1330
01:25:06,101 --> 01:25:10,109
You know, his son's a notorious playboy, and
I think he's asked everyone just to get you there.

1331
01:25:10,150 --> 01:25:12,697
- Uh, what's that?
- Nothing.

1332
01:25:12,781 --> 01:25:13,621
Show me.

1333
01:25:13,658 --> 01:25:16,204
I got you these. Remember?
You liked them in the shop.

1334
01:25:16,246 --> 01:25:20,254
Oh, my God. They must have cost you a fortune.

1335
01:25:22,425 --> 01:25:25,723
- Hello?
- I need to speak to you, Ian.

1336
01:25:27,435 --> 01:25:30,899
Kate, Kate, Kate, calm down.
What's the matter?

1337
01:25:30,942 --> 01:25:34,450
It's Terry. I really need to speak to you.

1338
01:25:34,532 --> 01:25:36,244
What, now?

1339
01:25:36,370 --> 01:25:38,457
Yeah, now. Is it possible?

1340
01:25:39,501 --> 01:25:41,839
Well, look,
I'll see what I can do.

1341
01:25:41,922 --> 01:25:43,843
I'll call you back,
all right?

1342
01:25:43,926 --> 01:25:48,101
- Is everything all right?
- Angela, I have to go to my brother's for a while.

1343
01:25:48,186 --> 01:25:50,523
- There's a little family problem.
- It's nothing serious, I hope.

1344
01:25:50,607 --> 01:25:52,694
No. That was Kate.
You remember? You met her.

1345
01:25:52,778 --> 01:25:55,700
It's just something's come up.
I'll see you back at yours in a while.

1346
01:25:55,784 --> 01:25:59,625
Well, hurry. I want to show you
my gratitude for the earrings.

1347
01:26:01,127 --> 01:26:04,676
All right. See you later, all right?

1348
01:26:06,472 --> 01:26:08,392
I'm worried about Terry, Ian.

1349
01:26:08,476 --> 01:26:10,605
What's the matter?

1350
01:26:10,647 --> 01:26:12,609
It's his mental health.

1351
01:26:12,652 --> 01:26:15,198
No, I know he was worried
about losing his job...

1352
01:26:15,240 --> 01:26:18,831
but we were just at the racetrack,
and he talked about starting the sport shop.

1353
01:26:18,913 --> 01:26:21,417
No, he's not
interested in that.

1354
01:26:21,460 --> 01:26:23,421
And now he's angry all the time.

1355
01:26:23,463 --> 01:26:25,968
- He's talking to himself, for God's sake.
- No, we decided.

1356
01:26:26,010 --> 01:26:29,725
He was gonna speak to Uncle Howard
about bankrolling it. He was very excited.

1357
01:26:29,810 --> 01:26:32,064
His mind's not right, Ian.

1358
01:26:32,148 --> 01:26:34,527
You know, what he says one minute
doesn't mean anything the next.

1359
01:26:34,611 --> 01:26:37,784
Right. Well, I'm- I'm taken aback.

1360
01:26:37,825 --> 01:26:40,706
It's all the pills he's taking,
and the drinking.

1361
01:26:40,790 --> 01:26:43,336
He thinks
he's killed someone.

1362
01:26:46,384 --> 01:26:47,846
- What?
- Yeah.

1363
01:26:47,888 --> 01:26:51,436
You know, I knew this girl once,
she had, like, mental problems.

1364
01:26:51,561 --> 01:26:54,234
She was convinced that
she had run someone over. She hadn't.

1365
01:26:54,317 --> 01:26:57,239
You know, but she was obsessed
with it for the rest of her life.

1366
01:26:57,323 --> 01:27:00,496
Does he, uh-
Is he going around...

1367
01:27:00,580 --> 01:27:05,130
talking- talking
about this, uh, murder?

1368
01:27:05,215 --> 01:27:09,014
He's gotten worse and worse.
He has these terrible nightmares.

1369
01:27:09,055 --> 01:27:12,187
He's uncommunicative,
face of doom all the time, bouts of crying.

1370
01:27:12,270 --> 01:27:15,318
When we were at the dog track,
he seemed to have come out of it.

1371
01:27:15,400 --> 01:27:18,491
When he come home,
he was straight back in it.

1372
01:27:18,574 --> 01:27:22,750
You know, it's just- it's obsession
that he's done this horrible thing.

1373
01:27:22,875 --> 01:27:25,046
And he- he won't
let me get a doctor.

1374
01:27:25,087 --> 01:27:28,177
No, no, don't do that.
Don't-Don't get a doctor.

1375
01:27:28,260 --> 01:27:32,562
If you get a doctor,
then it can- I'll deal with this.

1376
01:27:32,602 --> 01:27:33,026
Well, how?

1377
01:27:33,062 --> 01:27:35,901
Well, obviously, it's a bit
more serious than I thought...

1378
01:27:35,985 --> 01:27:40,409
but... if you get a doctor,
it could spiral out of control.

1379
01:27:40,450 --> 01:27:43,290
- I really think he should see a doctor.
- Don't get a doctor, Kate. Don't.

1380
01:27:43,373 --> 01:27:47,716
Because I know Terry, and it will
only make things worse. All right?

1381
01:27:47,756 --> 01:27:51,765
Just- I'm gonna be
in the countryside tomorrow, all right?

1382
01:27:51,849 --> 01:27:54,854
And then when I come back, I'll spend
some time with Terry, and it'll be-

1383
01:27:54,938 --> 01:27:56,859
You'll see. It'll be all right.

1384
01:27:56,942 --> 01:27:59,197
Well, where you gonna be
if I need you though?

1385
01:27:59,238 --> 01:28:01,534
I'll let you know my whereabouts,
then you can call me.

1386
01:28:01,619 --> 01:28:03,873
I'll come-
I'll come straight back.

1387
01:28:06,795 --> 01:28:09,927
- So you're a fan of the Greek tragedies too?
- Love them. Crazy about them.

1388
01:28:09,968 --> 01:28:12,765
It's just rare that I could ever
get the chance to act in one.

1389
01:28:12,849 --> 01:28:15,313
God, I know. It's difficult, isn't it?
Which is your favorite, Ian?

1390
01:28:15,355 --> 01:28:17,818
Oh, I'm not really
that-that familiar.

1391
01:28:17,901 --> 01:28:20,322
Oh, well. Mine's always been Medea,
Euripides.

1392
01:28:20,406 --> 01:28:24,498
Yeah, me too. I think Clytemnestra's
probably the best character...

1393
01:28:24,581 --> 01:28:26,501
- of all classical plays.
- Yeah.

1394
01:28:26,585 --> 01:28:28,965
I have to say, the best productions
of Greek myths I've ever seen-

1395
01:28:29,049 --> 01:28:31,303
better than anything you'll find
on the stage-was done in dance...

1396
01:28:31,387 --> 01:28:33,599
- by the Martha Graham troupe, you know them?
- Really?

1397
01:28:33,683 --> 01:28:36,939
Yeah. I mean, all the terror was there,
all the Aristotelian pity and fear.

1398
01:28:37,023 --> 01:28:39,861
It's so much more visceral
in dance, don't you think?

1399
01:28:39,897 --> 01:28:40,112
Right.

1400
01:28:40,196 --> 01:28:42,576
- Mr. Blaine? Your brother's here.
- Yeah?

1401
01:28:42,660 --> 01:28:44,580
- What?
- He'd like to see you.

1402
01:28:44,664 --> 01:28:48,044
Oh. Uh...

1403
01:28:48,087 --> 01:28:50,049
could you give me a moment?

1404
01:28:50,091 --> 01:28:51,099
Yeah, sure. Bring him in.

1405
01:28:51,135 --> 01:28:53,347
It must be pretty bad if he's
driven all the way out here.

1406
01:28:53,431 --> 01:28:58,022
No, I- Uh- It's just a little
family problem. I won't be long.

1407
01:29:00,485 --> 01:29:02,656
- Oh, I'm sure it's nothing.
- I'm sure.

1408
01:29:04,368 --> 01:29:06,665
- Your brother's there, Mr. Blaine.
- Thanks.

1409
01:29:14,806 --> 01:29:19,232
Terry, what are you doing here?
How did you know where I was?

1410
01:29:19,315 --> 01:29:21,236
Kate had the address.

1411
01:29:21,319 --> 01:29:24,242
- I need to tell you something.
- Well, just keep your voice down.

1412
01:29:24,325 --> 01:29:27,749
I don't want anyone overhearing.
Why didn't you just give me a phone?

1413
01:29:27,832 --> 01:29:30,671
- I want to turn myself in, Ian.
- What?

1414
01:29:30,755 --> 01:29:32,969
- We broke God's law.
- God?

1415
01:29:33,051 --> 01:29:36,767
Terry, what God?
What God, you idiot?

1416
01:29:36,851 --> 01:29:38,771
I shouldn't have let you
talk me into it.

1417
01:29:38,854 --> 01:29:42,780
- I didn't talk you into it. Stop deluding yourself.
- I want this off my neck.

1418
01:29:42,862 --> 01:29:45,326
Look, you can't do this,
Terry, all right?

1419
01:29:45,409 --> 01:29:49,166
You can't do it. You'd be throwing your whole
life away, and mine and Uncle Howard's.

1420
01:29:49,209 --> 01:29:52,048
I won't implicate
you and Howard.

1421
01:29:53,050 --> 01:29:55,013
- You won't-
- This is my personal decision.

1422
01:29:55,054 --> 01:29:57,475
- You won't be able to keep us out of it.
- I will.

1423
01:29:57,559 --> 01:29:59,479
No, you're upset.
You're unstable.

1424
01:29:59,564 --> 01:30:01,483
Your lies will be all transparent.

1425
01:30:01,568 --> 01:30:04,406
- I've thought about suicide, Ian.
- But why?

1426
01:30:04,448 --> 01:30:06,410
Stop asking the same
questions over and over.

1427
01:30:06,452 --> 01:30:08,999
Go and commit suicide,
and leave Howard and me out of it.

1428
01:30:09,082 --> 01:30:12,379
I just want the slate wiped clean.

1429
01:30:12,463 --> 01:30:14,759
Look. You're depressed.

1430
01:30:14,843 --> 01:30:17,639
You're just suffering
from a little depression, that's all.

1431
01:30:17,681 --> 01:30:21,732
- Kate wants me to see a doctor.
- No, no. Look, I can help you. If you'll just let me.

1432
01:30:21,769 --> 01:30:26,784
I just want to tell someone. Go in
and serve my punishment. Have it off me.

1433
01:30:26,825 --> 01:30:32,002
Just give me a minute. Give me a minute
to get my thoughts in order, will you?

1434
01:30:32,087 --> 01:30:36,010
I wish you could come with me.
But if you won't, I understand.

1435
01:30:36,052 --> 01:30:39,058
Just give me a minute.

1436
01:30:39,142 --> 01:30:42,273
- I feel less panic since I made this decision.
- Hi.

1437
01:30:42,356 --> 01:30:45,863
You okay?
Are you gonna join us?

1438
01:30:45,948 --> 01:30:49,830
Terry and I are just discussing a little problem.
Everything will be all right.

1439
01:30:49,913 --> 01:30:52,293
Just had to talk
to Ian about something.

1440
01:30:52,334 --> 01:30:54,297
- You sure?
- Yes.

1441
01:30:54,339 --> 01:30:57,053
You go on, I'll only be a minute.

1442
01:30:57,136 --> 01:30:59,057
Okay.

1443
01:31:03,064 --> 01:31:06,489
She's very beautiful.
She'd make a great wife for you.

1444
01:31:06,530 --> 01:31:07,198
Look, Terry.

1445
01:31:07,282 --> 01:31:09,578
Terry, listen to me.
I want to help you. I do.

1446
01:31:09,619 --> 01:31:11,582
But this is not
the time or the place.

1447
01:31:11,666 --> 01:31:13,795
- I'm sorry for barging in.
- No, no, it's all right. It's all right.

1448
01:31:13,878 --> 01:31:17,302
Look, I want to hear what you've got to say.
We're family. You're my brother.

1449
01:31:17,343 --> 01:31:19,640
Yeah, we can talk, but you're
not gonna change my mind.

1450
01:31:19,766 --> 01:31:24,901
Maybe not. Maybe not. Maybe you'll even
change mine. But just promise me one thing.

1451
01:31:25,026 --> 01:31:28,281
We've gotta have a discussion
about this before you plunge ahead.

1452
01:31:28,323 --> 01:31:30,870
- Promise?
- Promise. Can I come in and get a drink?

1453
01:31:30,953 --> 01:31:32,874
No, that's not a good idea.

1454
01:31:32,957 --> 01:31:36,547
- You go. I'll give you a call tonight.
- Right.

1455
01:31:40,764 --> 01:31:42,811
Call me tonight.

1456
01:32:04,019 --> 01:32:06,817
I just don't see any alternative.

1457
01:32:08,195 --> 01:32:10,324
What are we saying?

1458
01:32:10,408 --> 01:32:15,961
Well, I don't know what we're saying.
We're-We're saying we want to survive.

1459
01:32:17,171 --> 01:32:19,384
But he's family.

1460
01:32:19,469 --> 01:32:21,430
Terry. He's my brother.

1461
01:32:21,513 --> 01:32:23,434
Well, I-I know that.

1462
01:32:23,518 --> 01:32:29,028
But he has to be stopped before he-
this whole thing unravels.

1463
01:32:29,065 --> 01:32:31,533
Yeah, I can't-
I can't let that happen.

1464
01:32:31,618 --> 01:32:33,579
No.

1465
01:32:33,662 --> 01:32:36,084
No, I-

1466
01:32:36,168 --> 01:32:38,381
It's killing again.

1467
01:32:38,464 --> 01:32:40,885
How am I gonna do that?

1468
01:32:42,013 --> 01:32:44,684
It's deja vu,
but a thousand times worse.

1469
01:32:44,726 --> 01:32:46,687
Speed is of the essence.

1470
01:32:46,730 --> 01:32:51,197
Terry could be doing something awful
while we sit here and curse our fate.

1471
01:32:51,280 --> 01:32:54,495
He was right about one thing.

1472
01:32:54,538 --> 01:32:57,669
It was like crossing a line.

1473
01:32:57,752 --> 01:32:59,840
There was no way back.

1474
01:33:01,008 --> 01:33:03,806
It has to be made
to look like an accident.

1475
01:33:03,889 --> 01:33:09,150
Yeah. Yeah,
an accident or a suicide.

1476
01:33:11,572 --> 01:33:13,742
Well, he just broods.

1477
01:33:13,784 --> 01:33:16,915
You know, he sits there
talking to himself.

1478
01:33:17,000 --> 01:33:20,590
He imagines that you and him
have got some dark secret.

1479
01:33:20,673 --> 01:33:23,387
You know, that you've
harmed someone or something.

1480
01:33:24,472 --> 01:33:27,103
Ian, I think
he's gonna hurt himself.

1481
01:33:30,444 --> 01:33:32,990
Let me be alone
with him, Kate.

1482
01:33:33,072 --> 01:33:34,994
Yeah.

1483
01:33:54,074 --> 01:33:56,078
Terry.

1484
01:33:59,376 --> 01:34:03,717
- Terry.
- I had a dream about Martin Burns.

1485
01:34:17,997 --> 01:34:20,543
Terry, listen to me.

1486
01:34:20,626 --> 01:34:22,922
I dreamed again...

1487
01:34:23,007 --> 01:34:24,927
about Martin Burns.

1488
01:34:26,054 --> 01:34:28,517
You need a couple of days
away from all this.

1489
01:34:29,728 --> 01:34:33,694
Get some fresh air,
some sea air...

1490
01:34:33,777 --> 01:34:35,781
just the two of us.

1491
01:34:35,866 --> 01:34:38,537
We'll go out on the boat
again tomorrow.

1492
01:34:38,621 --> 01:34:41,627
- We never go sailing anymore, Ian.
- That's what I'm saying.

1493
01:34:42,963 --> 01:34:46,471
We'll take some sandwiches
and some beers...

1494
01:34:46,511 --> 01:34:51,103
and we'll just talk,
brother to brother.

1495
01:34:51,188 --> 01:34:53,150
I'd like that.

1496
01:34:54,152 --> 01:34:57,722
I wish you could see
my point of view.

1497
01:34:57,758 --> 01:35:01,291
It'll be great.
Just the two of us.

1498
01:35:02,795 --> 01:35:07,178
I think Angela said she was
taking Kate shopping tomorrow.

1499
01:35:07,303 --> 01:35:10,852
She said she was gonna
help her out with her style.

1500
01:35:10,888 --> 01:35:11,103
Yeah.

1501
01:35:11,187 --> 01:35:13,441
And we'll just relax, yeah?

1502
01:35:13,566 --> 01:35:17,155
Get some sun.
Maybe we can have a swim.

1503
01:35:17,240 --> 01:35:19,451
You'll feel so much better
when you've had some sea air.

1504
01:35:19,536 --> 01:35:22,667
Yeah, but we'll never
be our old selves again, Ian, right?

1505
01:35:22,709 --> 01:35:25,088
I mean, there's no going back.

1506
01:35:27,552 --> 01:35:31,518
Go and tell Kate that
we're going out sailing tomorrow.

1507
01:35:31,559 --> 01:35:33,230
- Right.
- Yeah.

1508
01:35:33,313 --> 01:35:35,233
- Okay.
- Come on.

1509
01:35:37,572 --> 01:35:42,206
Kate, I've got
something to tell you.

1510
01:35:42,289 --> 01:35:44,461
We're going sailing tomorrow.

1511
01:35:44,544 --> 01:35:47,843
Yeah, just the two of us.
Ian's gonna take me out on the boat.

1512
01:36:21,703 --> 01:36:23,622
So, did Terry tell you the good news?

1513
01:36:23,707 --> 01:36:26,378
Yeah, it's a wonderful idea.

1514
01:36:26,421 --> 01:36:30,345
'Cause you two never really got the chance
to spend much time on your boat, did you?

1515
01:36:30,428 --> 01:36:33,307
- And you were so excited when you first bought it.
- Yeah.

1516
01:36:33,392 --> 01:36:35,603
I told Ian about Angela taking you
shopping tomorrow as well.

1517
01:36:35,688 --> 01:36:38,109
Oh, yeah. She's so nice.

1518
01:36:42,577 --> 01:36:45,959
Mike Eisley from the garden party
asked if we were serious.

1519
01:36:46,000 --> 01:36:50,049
And then he invited me to
Morocco for the weekend.

1520
01:36:50,086 --> 01:36:51,678
And what did you say?

1521
01:36:51,763 --> 01:36:54,726
Well, I told him that I loved you.

1522
01:36:54,810 --> 01:36:59,151
For the first time in my life,
those words actually had meaning.

1523
01:36:59,235 --> 01:37:01,281
I love you.

1524
01:37:02,658 --> 01:37:04,622
- Are you all right?
- Yeah, yeah.

1525
01:37:04,662 --> 01:37:09,339
- You seem a bit distracted.
- No, I'm just thinking about what you're saying.

1526
01:37:09,464 --> 01:37:11,635
And I'm tired, you know.

1527
01:37:11,677 --> 01:37:14,808
Well, you have been
working really hard recently.

1528
01:37:16,019 --> 01:37:18,023
I think taking your boat
out with your brother...

1529
01:37:18,107 --> 01:37:21,363
will do you just
as much good as him.

1530
01:37:21,446 --> 01:37:24,829
- Is he all right?
- He's depressed.

1531
01:37:24,870 --> 01:37:28,794
He drinks too much
and he's getting sullen, and-

1532
01:37:28,837 --> 01:37:30,924
Kate's worried that
he might hurt himself.

1533
01:37:31,007 --> 01:37:33,513
Well, maybe he-
Well, he should go to a doctor then.

1534
01:37:33,549 --> 01:37:36,059
No, he resists. He resists.

1535
01:37:36,144 --> 01:37:40,318
I didn't tell Kate this,
but he's talked of suicide.

1536
01:37:40,359 --> 01:37:42,906
Oh, my God.

1537
01:37:45,161 --> 01:37:47,749
- I'm so sorry. That's awful.
- I know.

1538
01:39:39,639 --> 01:39:42,395
Best thing we ever did,
getting this boat, Terry, isn't it?

1539
01:39:42,478 --> 01:39:44,649
Eh?

1540
01:39:44,733 --> 01:39:47,864
Kate's right. We don't get out on it
as often as we should.

1541
01:39:47,906 --> 01:39:49,867
It's sad how things
turned out, isn't it?

1542
01:39:49,910 --> 01:39:53,625
- Don't start, Terry.
- No, I mean it, Ian.

1543
01:39:53,668 --> 01:39:55,629
We made the wrong decision.

1544
01:39:55,671 --> 01:39:58,260
The way I see it,
we didn't have much choice.

1545
01:39:58,344 --> 01:40:00,807
You always have choice, Ian.

1546
01:40:00,849 --> 01:40:03,646
I see that now.

1547
01:40:03,771 --> 01:40:05,650
I mean, I- I didn't at first.

1548
01:40:05,734 --> 01:40:10,327
I thought... like you,
that we had no choice, but-

1549
01:40:10,409 --> 01:40:12,957
All right, let's say that you're right-
which I'm not saying-

1550
01:40:12,998 --> 01:40:14,960
but let's say for
the sake of argument...

1551
01:40:15,002 --> 01:40:18,384
- that we did make the wrong choice.
- For the sake of argument?

1552
01:40:19,678 --> 01:40:21,641
You really fool yourself,
Ian, don't you?

1553
01:40:21,682 --> 01:40:25,189
His testimony was gonna put Uncle Howard
in prison for the rest of his life.

1554
01:40:25,271 --> 01:40:27,193
Well, maybe Uncle Howard
deserves to go to jail.

1555
01:40:27,275 --> 01:40:30,783
Oh, what a thing to say.
Forget it.

1556
01:40:30,867 --> 01:40:36,544
Christ, you think we've committed
some kind of unnatural act, but we haven't.

1557
01:40:36,628 --> 01:40:39,634
The whole of human life
is about violence.

1558
01:40:39,717 --> 01:40:42,390
It's a cruel world, Terry.

1559
01:40:42,473 --> 01:40:44,560
You're just shaken up
because you've come-

1560
01:40:44,644 --> 01:40:47,942
you've come face-to-face
with your own human nature.

1561
01:40:50,572 --> 01:40:54,497
I- I mean,
I didn't have to do it.

1562
01:40:54,539 --> 01:40:57,086
Well, why did you then?

1563
01:40:57,128 --> 01:41:02,639
I just kept going, like- like when
I gamble over my head, you know?

1564
01:41:02,722 --> 01:41:05,102
I just put the bet down
like when I'm in a dream.

1565
01:41:05,185 --> 01:41:07,316
You weren't dreaming
when you shot him.

1566
01:41:09,570 --> 01:41:11,574
All right. Look, listen.

1567
01:41:11,656 --> 01:41:14,162
We made a mistake, right? But it's over.

1568
01:41:14,246 --> 01:41:16,876
All right? We made the wrong choice.
I'm giving you that...

1569
01:41:16,959 --> 01:41:20,215
but being punished
by it won't undo it.

1570
01:41:20,300 --> 01:41:23,306
Martin Burns is dead.
He's dead.

1571
01:41:34,453 --> 01:41:36,415
I called the police last night.

1572
01:41:37,876 --> 01:41:40,339
You did what?

1573
01:41:40,421 --> 01:41:44,598
I called them and I told them I had
information on the murder of Martin Burns.

1574
01:41:44,681 --> 01:41:46,601
They said,
"Who is it?"

1575
01:41:46,685 --> 01:41:51,946
I wanted to tell them...
who I was, but I didn't.

1576
01:41:52,988 --> 01:41:55,202
Hung up.

1577
01:41:55,285 --> 01:41:57,915
I'm gonna call them
as soon as I get back, Ian.

1578
01:41:57,999 --> 01:42:00,546
Why would you do that?

1579
01:42:00,671 --> 01:42:05,055
What's the matter with you?
It's suicide, Terry.

1580
01:42:05,138 --> 01:42:09,272
Don't you even care that you're gonna take
Uncle Howard and me with you?

1581
01:42:09,355 --> 01:42:12,779
It's the order of things,
Ian. It's off kilter. Can't you see it?

1582
01:42:13,865 --> 01:42:16,453
I have to straighten it out.

1583
01:42:16,537 --> 01:42:21,379
All right. I don't wanna
talk about this anymore.

1584
01:42:21,463 --> 01:42:24,635
We came out here just to relax, didn't we?
Just to sail and unwind, eh?

1585
01:42:24,678 --> 01:42:27,433
Yeah.

1586
01:42:27,476 --> 01:42:30,815
- I'm gonna get us some more beers, all right?
- All right.

1587
01:43:52,896 --> 01:43:55,527
Why couldn't you just let it
go? Why couldn't you let it go?

1588
01:43:55,563 --> 01:43:56,237
Ian, what's wrong?

1589
01:43:56,319 --> 01:43:58,323
- You've ruined everything, Terry.
- Ian, what's wrong?

1590
01:43:58,366 --> 01:44:01,038
Terry, you've ruined it!
You've ruined everything!

1591
01:44:01,121 --> 01:44:04,628
- Ian, stop!
- We could've had everything!

1592
01:44:08,803 --> 01:44:11,015
Ian. Ian.

1593
01:44:12,058 --> 01:44:14,187
Ian. Ian.

1594
01:44:15,190 --> 01:44:17,862
Ian.

1595
01:44:20,075 --> 01:44:22,037
Ian!

1596
01:44:23,081 --> 01:44:25,294
Oh, God.

1597
01:44:30,638 --> 01:44:32,600
God.

1598
01:44:39,405 --> 01:44:42,203
What we think happened,
but we don't know for sure...

1599
01:44:42,244 --> 01:44:45,334
one killed the other,
either on purpose or by accident...

1600
01:44:45,417 --> 01:44:49,342
and then took his own life,
drowned himself.

1601
01:44:49,426 --> 01:44:51,722
Awful.

1602
01:44:51,764 --> 01:44:54,685
The place reeks of booze and pills.

1603
01:44:54,770 --> 01:44:57,817
I don't know.
Every day, it's something else.

1604
01:45:04,289 --> 01:45:07,462
Oh, I like that.

1605
01:45:07,545 --> 01:45:09,466
- What do you think?
- Yeah.

1606
01:45:09,549 --> 01:45:11,470
- I would look good in that.
- Yeah, Terry would love that.

1607
01:45:11,512 --> 01:45:14,017
- Would he?
- Yeah, men love that sort of shape.

1608
01:45:14,100 --> 01:45:17,190
I wore something similar
when Ian first saw me.
